Clean Data

df = read.csv('poly_for_reg.csv')
df <- xts(df[,colnames(df)!="Week"], order.by=as.Date(df$Week,"%Y-%m-%d"))
df$AvgFeeUsd_growth <- diff(log(df$AvgFeeUsd))
df$AvgTxCnt_growth <- diff(log(df$AvgTxCnt))
df$AvgPriceUSD_growth <- diff(log(df$AvgPriceUSD))
df$Interest_growth <- diff(log(df$Interest))

Plot Data to 2X Check it is Staionary

Given the chosen model, look for a structural break using QLR

df$AvgFeeUsd_growth_l1<- stats::lag(df$AvgFeeUsd_growth,k=1,na.pad=T)
df$AvgFeeUsd_growth_l2<- stats::lag(df$AvgFeeUsd_growth,k=2,na.pad=T)
df$AvgFeeUsd_growth_l3<- stats::lag(df$AvgFeeUsd_growth,k=3,na.pad=T)
df$AvgFeeUsd_growth_l4<- stats::lag(df$AvgFeeUsd_growth,k=4,na.pad=T)
df$AvgFeeUsd_growth_l5<- stats::lag(df$AvgFeeUsd_growth,k=5,na.pad=T)
df$AvgFeeUsd_growth_l6<- stats::lag(df$AvgFeeUsd_growth,k=6,na.pad=T)

F_values <- Fstats(AvgFeeUsd_growth ~ AvgFeeUsd_growth_l1 + AvgFeeUsd_growth_l2 + AvgFeeUsd_growth_l3 + AvgFeeUsd_growth_l4 + AvgFeeUsd_growth_l5 + AvgFeeUsd_growth_l6 +  Interest_growth, data = as.data.frame(df), from = 0.15, to = 0.85, vcov = function(x, ...) vcovHC(x, type = "HC", ...))
F_values$breakpoint

plot(F_values$Fstats)
lines(breakpoints(F_values))
